The paper focuses on improving the accuracy of human parsing, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel adversarial network architecture, which involves training multiple discriminators to address different types of parsing inconsistency. This suggests that the paper may also belong to sub-categories related to machine learning and neural networks, such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper involves semantic segmentation, which is a sub-task of image understanding and analysis, suggesting that it may also belong to sub-categories such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.MM (Multimedia).
